rephrased.body:
The table `point_2d` contains the x and y coordinates of unique points in a plane. Your task is to write a SQL query to find the shortest distance between any two distinct points. The result should be rounded to 2 decimal places.

Table Schema:
sql
CREATE TABLE point_2d (x INT, y INT);
INSERT INTO point_2d (x, y) VALUES (-1, -1);
INSERT INTO point_2d (x, y) VALUES (0, 0);
INSERT INTO point_2d (x, y) VALUES (-1, -2);
